olive oil
2 Kumara
1 carrot
1 beetroot
1 sachet Mild North Indian Spice Blend
1 packet flaked almonds
½ lime
1 packet mayonnaise
1 packet chicken thigh
1 sachet Sri Lankan spice blend
1 tsp honey
1 packet mint

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced. Peel kumara. Cut kumara and carrot into bite-sized chunks. Cut beeroot into 1cm chunks.
• Place veggies on a lined oven tray. Sprinkle over mild North Indian spice blend, drizzle with olive oil and toss to coat. Season with salt and pepper.
• Spread out evenly, then roast until tender, 25-30 minutes.

• Meanwhile, heat a large frying pan over medium-high heat. Toast flaked almonds, tossing, until golden, 2-3 minutes. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.
• Zest lime to get a pinch and slice into wedges. In a small bowl, combine mayonnaise and lime zest. Season with salt and pepper. Set aside.
• In a medium bowl, combine chicken thigh, Sri Lankan spice blend, a pinch of salt and a drizzle of olive oil.

• Return frying pan to medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Cook chicken until browned, 2 minutes each side.
• Transfer chicken to a second lined oven tray and drizzle with the honey. Bake until cooked through, 12-14 minutes.

TIP: Chicken is cooked through when it's no longer pink inside.

• When roast veggies are done, add a generous squeeze of lime juice to the tray. Gently toss to combine. Season to taste.
• Slice Sri Lankan-spiced chicken.
• Divide roast veggie toss between plates. Top with chicken.
• Spoon over lime mayo. Garnish with toasted almonds and tear over mint. Serve with any remaining lime wedges. Enjoy!